e faster, to maybe give him a hearing, maybe get them on your side?



 MR. EARNEST: Well, we certainly have made the case to all 100 senators t=
hat they have a basic responsibility that's dictated by the Constitution =
whether they're on our side or not. And right now, we've seen too many Re=
publican senators indicate that they're not prepared to do their job, tha=
